name: ID
label: ID
description: Semi-colon separated list of unique identifiers where available

name: REF
label: REF
description: The value in the POS field refers to the position of the first base in the String

name: ALT
label: ALT
description: Comma separated list of alternate non-reference alleles called on at least one of the samples

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_AMR_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_AMR_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for American population in ExAC (AC_AMR/AN_AMR)

name: INFO_ExAC_AF
label: INFO_ExAC_AF
description: Raw allele frequency (population independent) of the variant based on ExAC exomes (AF)

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_NFE_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_NFE_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for Non-Finnish European population in ExAC (AC_NFE/AN_NFE)

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency (population independent) of the variant based on ExAC (AC_Adj/AN_Adj)

name: VEP_HGVSc_transcript
label: VEP_HGVSc_transcript
description: for use in HGVSc notation (left part before period glyph)

name: VEP_HGVSp_transcript
label: VEP_HGVSp_transcript
description: for use in HGVSp notation (left part before period glyph)

name: VEP_Zygosity
label: VEP_Zygosity
description: Heterozygous, Homozygous, Hemizygous, Unknown. Indels considered equal for zygosity

name: VEP_HGVS_OFFSET
label: VEP_HGVS_OFFSET
description: HGVS was calculated after ambiguous repeat shift. Column shows shift size

name: VEP_IMPACT
label: VEP_IMPACT
description: high impact, changed protein effectiveness , no change, no evidence or difficult to predict

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_SAS_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_SAS_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for South Asian population in ExAC (AC_SAS/AN_SAS)

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_EAS_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_EAS_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for East Asian population in ExAC (AC_EAS/AN_EAS)

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_AFR_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_AFR_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for African/African American population in ExAC (AC_AFR/AN_AFR)

name: VEP_SYMBOL
label: VEP_SYMBOL
description: Gene ID in database from "Gene DB" column

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_OTH_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_OTH_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for Other population in ExAC (AC_OTH/AN_OTH)

name: INFO_TYPE
label: INFO_TYPE
description: The type of variant (snp or indel).

name: VEP_VARIANT_CLASS
label: VEP_VARIANT_CLASS
description: SNV (single nucleotide variant), insertion, deletion, indel, MNP (multiple nucleotide polymorphism), MNV (multiple nucleotide variant), duplication, sequence alteration, inversion, microsatellite, monomeric repeat, CNL (copy number loss), CNG (copy number gain), CNV (copy number variation), MEI (mobile element insertion), NSI (novel sequence insertion), complex, tandem duplication, translocation, no variation

name: VEP_SIFT
label: VEP_SIFT
description: SIFT v5.2.2. Lower score is more likely deleterious. Common threshold is 0.05

name: VEP_Genotype
label: VEP_Genotype
description: Capital case is for alternative alleles and lowercase is for reference allele

name: INFO_ExAC_AF_FIN_Adj
label: INFO_ExAC_AF_FIN_Adj
description: Adjusted allele frequency of the variant for Finnish population in ExAC (AC_FIN/AN_FIN)

name: VEP_BIOTYPE
label: VEP_BIOTYPE
description: Gene type in Havana DB. Protein coding: IGC gene, IGD gene, IG gene, IGJ gene, IGLV gene, IGM gene, IGV gene, IGZ gene, nonsense mediated decay, nontranslating CDS, non stop decay, polymorphic pseudogene, TRC gene, TRD gene, TRJ gene. Pseudogene: disrupted domain, IGC pseudogene, IGJ pseudogene, IG pseudogene, IGV pseudogene, processed pseudogene, transcribed processed pseudogene, transcribed unitary pseudogene, transcribed unprocessed pseudogene, translated processed pseudogene, TRJ pseudogene, unprocessed pseudogene. Long noncoding: 3prime overlapping ncrna, ambiguous orf, antisense, antisense RNA, lincRNA, ncrna host, processed transcript, sense intronic, sense overlapping. Short noncoding: miRNA, miRNA_pseudogene, miscRNA, miscRNA pseudogene, Mt rRNA, Mt tRNA, rRNA, scRNA, snlRNA, snoRNA, snRNA, tRNA, tRNA_pseudogene

name: VEP_PolyPhen
label: VEP_PolyPhen
description: PolyPhen-2 v2.2.2. Probability(variation is deleterious). Common threshold is 0.95

name: INFO_ADP
label: INFO_ADP
description: Average per-sample depth of bases with Phred score >= 0

name: INFO_SAR
label: INFO_SAR
description: Alternate allele observations on the reverse strand

name: INFO_AF
label: INFO_AF
description: Allele frequency based on Flow Evaluator observation counts

name: INFO_FSAF
label: INFO_FSAF
description: Flow Evaluator Alternate allele observations on the forward strand

name: INFO_SAF
label: INFO_SAF
description: Alternate allele observations on the forward strand

name: INFO_FSAR
label: INFO_FSAR
description: Flow Evaluator Alternate allele observations on the reverse strand

name: INFO_PB
label: INFO_PB
description: Bias of relative variant position in reference reads versus variant reads. Equals Mann-Whitney U rho statistic P(Y>X)+0.5P(Y=X)

name: INFO_HS
label: INFO_HS
description: Indicate it is at a hot spot

name: INFO_STB
label: INFO_STB
description: Strand bias in variant relative to reference.

name: INFO_DP
label: INFO_DP
description: Total read depth at the locus

name: INFO_PBP
label: INFO_PBP
description: Pval of relative variant position in reference reads versus variant reads.  Related to GATK ReadPosRankSumTest

name: INFO_FSRF
label: INFO_FSRF
description: Flow Evaluator Reference observations on the forward strand

name: INFO_RBI
label: INFO_RBI
description: Distance of bias parameters from zero.

name: INFO_TYPE
label: INFO_TYPE
description: The type of allele, either snp, mnp, ins, del, or complex.

name: INFO_FSRR
label: INFO_FSRR
description: Flow Evaluator Reference observations on the reverse strand

name: INFO_FDP
label: INFO_FDP
description: Flow Evaluator read depth at the locus

name: INFO_HRUN
label: INFO_HRUN
description: Run length: the number of consecutive repeats of the alternate allele in the reference genome

name: INFO_SRF
label: INFO_SRF
description: Number of reference observations on the forward strand

name: INFO_SRR
label: INFO_SRR
description: Number of reference observations on the reverse strand

name: INFO_FR
label: INFO_FR
description: Reason why the variant was filtered.

name: INFO_STBP
label: INFO_STBP
description: Pval of Strand bias in variant relative to reference.

name: INFO_OMAPALT
label: INFO_OMAPALT
description: Maps OID,OPOS,OREF,OALT entries to specific ALT alleles

name: INFO_GPV
label: INFO_GPV
description: Fisher's Exact Test P-value of tumor+normal versus no variant for Germline calls

name: INFO_SSC
label: INFO_SSC
description: Somatic score in Phred scale (0-255) derived from somatic p-value

name: INFO_SOMATIC
label: INFO_SOMATIC
description: Indicates if record is a somatic mutation

name: INFO_SPV
label: INFO_SPV
description: Fisher's Exact Test P-value of tumor versus normal for Somatic/LOH calls

name: INFO_EUR_AF
label: INFO_EUR_AF
description: Allele frequency in the EUR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

name: INFO_MULTI_ALLELIC
label: INFO_MULTI_ALLELIC
description: indicates whether a site is multi-allelic

name: INFO_SAS_AF
label: INFO_SAS_AF
description: Allele frequency in the SAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

name: INFO_AN
label: INFO_AN
description: Total number of alleles in called genotypes

name: INFO_AC
label: INFO_AC
description: Total number of alternate alleles in called genotypes

name: INFO_EAS_AF
label: INFO_EAS_AF
description: Allele frequency in the EAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

name: INFO_AMR_AF
label: INFO_AMR_AF
description: Allele frequency in the AMR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

name: INFO_EX_TARGET
label: INFO_EX_TARGET
description: indicates whether a variant is within the exon pull down target boundaries

name: INFO_AFR_AF
label: INFO_AFR_AF
description: Allele frequency in the AFR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

name: INFO_VT
label: INFO_VT
description: indicates what type of variant the line represents

name: INFO_SGANNOT
label: INFO_SGANNOT
description: Location-based Annotation: Coding Sequence(CDS),3'UTR(U3),5'UTR(U5),Acceptor Splice Site(AS),Donor Splice Site(DS),Intron(INT),Intergenic Region(ING)
